@node intro "Introduction.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Intro
  ~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   This program is a simple sample converter that can convert samples
   from IFF-8SVX (mono/stereo) to IFF-8SVX, RAW (header less), AIFF,
   WAVE or VOC files. It features a MUI GUI.

   @{u}It can convert IFF-8SVX to:@{uu}

   * IFF-8SVX     - mono/stereo
   * RAW          - mono/stereo, 8/16 bit, motorola/intel, signed
   * Audio IFF    - mono/stereo, 8/12/16 bit
   * RIFF-WAVE    - mono/stereo, 8/12/16 bit, PCM
   * RIFX-WAVE    - as RIFF but in motorola-format, rarely used
   * Creative VOC - mono/stereo  8/12/16 bit, PCM, v1.20

   While converting it is also possible to switch between mono and
   stereo and resample the sample. It has hand-optimized assembler
   routines for converting the samples as fast as possible.

   @{u}It can resample the samples to:@{uu}
   
   * Not at all
   * Half the frequency
   * Double the frequency
   * Resample to a custom frequency
   * resample to 11025 Hz
   * resample to 16000 Hz
   * resample to 22050 Hz
   * resample to 32000 Hz
   * resample to 44100 Hz
   * resample to 48000 Hz

   The program also has a listview for converting many files at the
   same time.


@endnode

@node install "Installation.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Installation
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   It doesn't need installation. Just copy the program or the drawer
   wherever your like.


@endnode

@node req "Requirements.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Requirements
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   OS V37+                   - Works on V50+ too
   MUI  v3.x                 - I'm not really sure about the version here.. ;-)
   Asl.library v37           - Only required when using file-requester
   MathIEEEDoubTrans.library - Only required when converting to AIFF
   SetPatch v43+             - I know it crashes with v40.16 (1994-02-14) (math bug..)

   A couple of 100kB of memory..


@endnode

@node usage "Usage.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}Usage
  ~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   The program has a GUI with a numerous of gadgets, but it can be
   use from CLI as well, see below:

   @{b}Status:@{ub}      - Shows info about the input file and general status.

   @{b}Input File:@{ub}  - This is where you specify the IFF-file to convert.

   @{b}Output File:@{ub} - This is the resulting file (or path when using the
                  batch list).

   @{fg fill}-- Fileformat --@{fg text}

   @{b}Save Format:@{ub} - Here you select which file format you want your
                  output file to be in.

   @{b}i@{ub}            - This gives some info about the selected saveformat.

   @{b}Mode:@{ub}        - Select if you want to save in Mono or Stereo.
                  Note that if you convert a stereo-file to mono the
                  left channel will be used!  If you set this to Auto,
                  all files will be converted to the same mode that the
                  sources file are in. Useful when using the list.

   @{b}ReSample:@{ub}    - Here you can set if you want to resample the input file.

   @{b}HiQ@{ub}          - If resampling should be done in high quality.
                  Linear interpolation is used.

   @{fg fill}-- Dataformat --@{fg text}

   @{b}Bits:@{ub}        - The bit-resolution of the output file.

   @{b}ByteOrder:@{ub}   - This toggles if you want to save in Motorola (MSB first)
                  or Intel (LSB first).
                  Note that if you save a WAV in motorola it will be an
                  RIFX-WAVE file which are rarely used, use intel instead!

   @{b}Format@{ub}       - If the output should be in signed or unsigned in
                  the RAW format.

   @{fg fill}----- List -----@{fg text}

   @{b}Use@{ub}          - This toggle if you want to use the file list instead
                  of converting single files.
                  Note that if you're using a list, the Output File will
                  contain the destination directory for all files!

   @{b}Lister@{ub}       - Brings you to the file list.

   @{fg fill}--- Project ----@{fg text}

   @{b}Abort@{ub}        - Used to abort an operation.

   @{b}Convert@{ub}      - This will execute whatever you have setup the program
                  to do. Convert the sample or list of samples.

   @{b}About@{ub}        - Shows information about the program.

   @{b}Quit@{ub}         - Exits the program and saves the gadget states.


  @{fg shine}@{b}CLI Usage
  Ā~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   The template when running 8SVXtoXXX from CLI is:

   INPUT/K/A,OUTPUT/K/A

   When specifying an input- and an output file on the commandline
   8SVXtoXXX will immediately convert the sample using the settings
   from the GUI without opening the GUI. When it is finished it will
   immediately quit.


  @{fg shine}@{b}Some notes..
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   This program is made in Amiga-E with the resample- and save-routines
   in optimized assembler, this increases the speed about 3 times!

   I don't know if the RIFX-WAVE (motorola-version of RIFF-WAVE) is
   saved right because I have no program that can read it.
   However, the other formats has been tested with AudioMaster IV,
   Play16 v1.9 and Lame mpeg-encoder.

   If you resample a file which frequency is less than 1% from
   the original it wouldn't be resampled, just labeled with the
   new frequency!
   Ex. Resample "bla.iff" which is saved in 31960 Hz (from f.ex AudioMaster)
       to 32000Hz will not resample the file, just label it 32000Hz.


@endnode

@node news "News.."

  @{fg shine}@{b}News and Changes
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}* NEW *@{fg text} Now 8SVXtoXXX can be used from CLI.

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Fixed reading of file headers. It could easily crash
           before if a file wasn't as expected.

   @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Raised the internal stack a bit to make it more stable on OS4.

   @{fg fill}* NEW *@{fg text} I finally made a guide :)

 @{b}v1.31
 ~~~~~@{ub}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} I have made some mistakes in the WAV-header. The blockalign-field was
     not set f.ex. WAVs should work better on Windows Media Player now.
     Thanks to Roy Buckley for reporting the problems and help me debug!
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The program always saved prefs when exiting, now it only "uses"
     (saving to ENV: instead of ENVARC:) the prefs when quitting.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added menu options for explicitly saving the prefs and loading
     the last saved.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a couple of button-ghosting bugs. F.ex. Format was not
     editable the way it should have. It should only be selectable
     for 8-bit RAW. All other formats are defined to one or the
     other. I have seen no program that uses 16-bit unsigned, therefor
     is this not editable even with RAW.

 @{b}v1.3
 ~~~~@{ub}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a long standing bug which made the header say that
     samples that was resampled was a few bytes longer or shorter
     than they actually are. This should now have been fixed!
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can resample to any frequency, not just the pre-defined.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a bug in the WAV header.
   
 @{b}v1.2a
 ~~~~~@{ub}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a bug when converting some stereo samples.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Minor cosmetic changes.
   
 @{b}v1.2
 ~~~~@{ub}
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} I have made it possible to control most of the program using the
     keyboard.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed the ghosting of some cycle gadgets that was ghosted when
     the shouldn't and not ghosted when they should.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} I gave the program a menu and the option to get to the MUI settings.
   
   @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The Output File now changes the extension when cycling through the
     save format.


@endnode

